Using `lxml`, you can apply an XSLT-1.0 stylesheet which ignores the element that should be removed being passed a parameter to the stylesheet. The rest of the file is copied by the _identity template_ and the unnecessary spaces are removed by `xsl:strip-space`.

Here the parameter is passed by `remov`(=`RatePlanEnum`):

    remov = ET.XSLT.strparam(&#39;RatePlanEnum&#39;)  

The XSLT-1.0 stylesheet (`remove.xslt`):

    &lt;?xml version=&quot;1.0&quot; encoding=&quot;UTF-8&quot;?&gt;
    &lt;xsl:stylesheet version=&quot;1.0&quot; xmlns:xsl=&quot;http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Transform&quot; xmlns:xs=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema&quot;&gt;
        &lt;xsl:output method=&quot;xml&quot; omit-xml-declaration=&quot;no&quot; indent=&quot;yes&quot;/&gt;
        &lt;xsl:strip-space elements=&quot;*&quot; /&gt;
        &lt;xsl:param name=&quot;toRemove&quot; /&gt;
    
        &lt;xsl:template match=&quot;node()|@*&quot;&gt;
            &lt;xsl:copy&gt;
                &lt;xsl:apply-templates select=&quot;node()|@*&quot; /&gt;
            &lt;/xsl:copy&gt;
        &lt;/xsl:template&gt;
       
        &lt;xsl:template match=&quot;xs:simpleType&quot;&gt;
            &lt;xsl:if test=&quot;@name != $toRemove&quot;&gt;
                &lt;xsl:copy&gt;
                    &lt;xsl:apply-templates select=&quot;node()|@*&quot; /&gt;
                &lt;/xsl:copy&gt;
            &lt;/xsl:if&gt;
        &lt;/xsl:template&gt;
    
    &lt;/xsl:stylesheet&gt;

The Python code to call this stylesheet could be:

    import lxml.etree as ET
    
    # Parse XML and XSLT
    dom = ET.parse(input_xml_filename)
    xslt = ET.parse(&#39;remove.xslt&#39;)
    transform = ET.XSLT(xslt)
    # Set the parameter which specifies the element to be removed
    remov = ET.XSLT.strparam(&#39;RatePlanEnum&#39;)
    result = transform(dom, toRemove=remov)
    
    # Print the result
    print(ET.tostring(result, pretty_print=True))

This file uses namespace `xmlns:xs=&quot;http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema&quot;` and you have to use `{http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema}` instead of `xs:` in `findall()`

     doc.findall(&#39;.//{http://www.w3.org/2001/XMLSchema}simpleType&#39;):


Doc: [lxml - Namespaces](https://lxml.de/tutorial.html#namespaces)

---

Full example:

