There is no filter query to achieve this directly. Only thing you can do is to use aggregation framework and achieve your desired result. First you have to unwind the `grades` array, then you filter all the documents with `score` greater than 60, then group by `_id` along with that use `$push` re-create array of `grades`, then again use  `match` to filter only documents with `grades` array size of `n`.


Below query works for documents with n=4

    [{
        $unwind: {
            path: &quot;$grades&quot;
        }
    }, {
        $match: {
            &quot;grades.age&quot;: {
                $gte: 60
            }
        }
    }, {
        $group: {
            _id: &quot;$_id&quot;,
            grades: {
                $push: &quot;$grades&quot;
            }
        }
    }, {
        $match: {
            &quot;grades&quot;: {
                $size: 4
            }
        }
    }]

